place.name: HARTCLIFFE
place.gazetteerText: HARTCLIFFE-WITH-BEDMINSTER, a hundred in the NW of Somerset; adjacent to Gloucestershire; and containing Bedminster parish, and six other parishes. Acres, 18, 377. Pop. in 1851, 6, 572; in 1861, 6, 879. Houses, 1, 265. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)

place.name: STOCKWOOD
place.gazetteerText: Stockwood House, seat, in NE. of Somerset, 3 miles SE. of Bristol. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)
